dcterms:description: This dataset was collected from 2009 to 2010 using the ASSISTment system. It contains the interactions of 3002 learners and 17,705 items associated with 123 skills, forming 277,540 interaction records.

dcterms:description: This dataset, which updates Assist0910, was collected over the whole year of 2012. In this dataset, 22,339 learners in the system attempted 52,825 mathematics questions requiring 265 skills. This dataset contains the largest number of learners, questions, and interaction entries (nearly 2.7 million). It is a one-skill-per-question dataset, meaning that each question requires one skill.
dcterms:title: Assist1213

dcterms:description: The EdNet dataset is newly available to the public. Following previous studies, 5000 students who answered 12,372 questions requiring 188 skills were randomly selected, thus obtaining 347,866 interaction logs. This dataset contains the minimum number of attempted items per learner.
dcterms:title: EdNet
